<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.181140>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8 – 16. Eretmocerus cocois Delvare sp. n. (Ψ: Figs 8, 10 – 16; ♂: Fig. 9). 8. Female habitus. 9. Male habitus. 10. Antenna. 11. Pedicel and funicle. 12. Apex of clava. 13. Mid tarsus. 14. Fore wing. 15. Base of fore wing. 16. Submarginal vein enlarged." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/181140/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.181141>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17 – 22. Figs 17 – 20. Ψ Eretmocerus cocois Delvare sp. n. 17. Head in frontal view. 18. Mesonotum. 19. Scutellum. 20. Ovipositor. Figs 21 – 22. Ψ Eretmocerus gracilis Rose. 21. Head in frontal view. 22. Antenna." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/181141/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

